close_reason: "Resolved: 126 flat specs nested into src-mirrored subdirs; all dirs well under the 120 cap; static gate directory_load=0."
body: "## tests/unit directory-density pressure — RESOLVED by module-mirrored nesting\n\n### Problem (as filed)\ntests/unit/ held spec files flat in a single directory, reaching 126 files against the static-quality-gate cap of --max-files-per-dir 120. CI Gates(static) (scripts/release/static-quality-gate.mjs checkDirectoryLoad) fails when any directory exceeds the cap. Zero headroom remained; every new spec risked breaking CI.\n\n### Resolution\nImplemented ADR pm-kjmx: all 126 root specs were nested into src-mirrored subdirectories (commands/, cli/, core/<sub>/, extensions/, mcp/, sdk/, packages/, scripts/). Post-reorg per-directory counts are all well under the cap (largest: tests/unit/commands at 50, tests/unit/core/item at 14). The cap is now satisfied structurally rather than by ad-hoc consolidation. Static quality gate verified green (ok: true, directory_load violations = 0).\n\n### Follow-up\nConvention is documented in ADR pm-kjmx so future specs are placed in the correct src-mirrored subdirectory and density stays bounded by design."
